HEADWORD: Crants
<hw>Crants</hw> <pr>(kr⟦acr⟧nts)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. D.
<ets>krans</ets>, G. <ets>kranz</ets>.]</ety> <def>A garland carried
before the bier of a maiden.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Yet here she is allowed her virgin <qex>crants</qex>, Her maiden
strewments.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crap</ent>⟦br⟧
